org.youscope.plugin.lifecelldetection

Interface CellDetectionJob

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Component, EditableJobContainer, ImageProducer, Job, JobContainer, java.rmi.Remote, TableProducer

    public interface CellDetectionJob
extends Job, ImageProducer, TableProducer, EditableJobContainer
    This job detects cells in the image passed to it. It passes information about the detected cells to its table listeners. If configured respectively, it also produces an image in which the detected cells are highlighted to its image listeners.
    Author:
    Moritz Lang

      • addSegmentationImageListener

        void addSegmentationImageListener(ImageListener listener)
                           throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Adds a listener which is invoked if a new segmentation image was created. A listener can always be added, even if the respective measurement is already running. Note: if the cells are not visualized, this is the same as adding the listener with addImageListener().
        Parameters:
        listener - Listener which should be notified.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException

      • setMinimalTimeMS

        void setMinimalTimeMS(long minimalTimeMS)
               throws MeasurementRunningException,
                      java.rmi.RemoteException
        Sets the minimal time (in ms) the execution of the job should take. If the execution of the job takes less, the rest of the time span will be waited. This function is mainly ment for real-time applications.
        Parameters:
        minimalTimeMS - The minimal time in ms the execution of the job has to take, or -1.
        Throws:
        MeasurementRunningException
        java.rmi.RemoteException
